{"v":1,"id":"2Bx7nYjtZW64lVnX3KJB","createdAt":"2026-06-14T10:20:34.633Z","app":{"name":"AxiVale","version":"0.4.0"},"kind":"conversation","title":"review the latest raid","turns":[{"userText":"review the latest raid","agentText":"\n\nGood data — latest raid is Dub Grumble's June 13 run. Let me render the chart to complete the review.\n\n---\n\n## Evenly split night against a larger enemy — strip game elite, but the squad isn't resetting when it should.\n\nDub Grumble's June 13 raid is the **first logged run** under this tag in the system. 18 fights, 9W/9L (50%), consistently outnumbered — squad averaged **40 vs. 49 enemies** per engagement. Squad KDR came in at **0.70** (246 enemy deaths vs. 349 squad deaths), which is respectable given the numbers disadvantage but leaves clear room to improve.\n\nTop down contributors across the night — the squad's raw fighting spine held up:\n\n{{figure}}\n\n| Date | Fights | W/L | KDR | Squad Deaths | Squad Downs | Top Healer |\n|------|--------|-----|-----|-------------|-------------|------------|\n| Jun 13 | 18 | 9/9 | 0.70 | 349 | 560 | Aeri.4529 (6.7M) |\n\n*(Single run on record for this tag — trend view will build as more nights are logged.)*\n\n{{figure}}\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Strengths\n\n- **Elite DPS trio:** BreakN.5496 (Berserker, 1.08M down contrib), DraGonfly.9317 (1.05M), and Fibbs.1623 (Tempest, 890k) are the squad's backbone — top-end output competitive against much larger forces.\n- **Strip coordination is a real weapon:** Mes.1906 (Reaper, 1,223 strips) and Jax Blake (968 strips) combined for **2,191 boon strips** — one of the squad's clearest tactical edges, and it showed in the 9 wins.\n- **Healer depth:** Aeri.4529 (Druid, 6.7M healing, 2,636 cleanses) and Arx.9785 (2,417 cleanses) carried sustain through repeated outnumbered fights. Five Druids in total gave the squad strong anchor coverage.\n\n---\n\n### 🎯 Coaching Points\n\n- **No reset call:** 35 of 47 players logged 7–9 deaths across 18 fights — the squad isn't getting the disengage signal in time. When a losing fight drags, the whole squad bleeds deaths rather than resetting. KDR of 0.70 is the result.\n- **Fight selection against 22% larger forces:** Averaging 40v49 all night isn't always avoidable, but some engagements should be passed on. Winning half is solid; winning 60%+ requires picking terrain and timing better, not just outfighting the numbers.\n- **hotep.8715 positioning:** Troubadour role (boon support), but led the roster with **24 downs and 10 deaths** — the most exposed player in the squad. A support getting downed that frequently breaks the boon loop at critical moments. Needs explicit positioning coaching to stay inside the zerg.\n- **Kaliptuce.9051 (Firebrand):** 22 downs, 9 deaths, only **147 cleanses** — well below what a support Firebrand should produce (Aeri had 2,636). Either misplaced as an offensive FB in a support slot, or rotation is off. Clarify the role expectation.\n\n---\n\n**Double down on:** Calling coordinated strip windows with Mes.1906 and Jax Blake — 2,191 combined strips is elite and the clearest reason the squad wins outnumbered.\n\n**Change:** Introduce an explicit reset call threshold. When the squad is losing a fight and deaths start stacking, Dub Grumble needs to disengage before the wipe — the death distribution shows the squad is fighting to the last player too often.","filedAt":"3:09 AM","tools":[{"name":"ToolSearch"},{"name":"axibridge_runs_list"},{"name":"axibridge_commander_stats","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title":"Commanders","columns":[{"key":"account","label":"Commander"},{"key":"fightsLed","label":"Fights led"},{"key":"wins","label":"W"},{"key":"losses","label":"L"},{"key":"kdr","label":"KDR"},{"key":"deaths","label":"Deaths"}],"rows":[{"account":"harasho.4281","profession":"Troubadour","runs":19,"fightsLed":314,"wins":196,"losses":118,"kdr":1.29,"kills":5998,"deaths":100},{"account":"bro.2856","profession":"Troubadour","runs":10,"fightsLed":249,"wins":114,"lo